# Path prefixes to skip when analyzing a target (often used with target `.` = repo root).
# One path per line, relative to the **directory being analyzed**. Lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Typical use: exclude dependencies, generated assets, virtualenvs, and other large trees
# so analysis stays fast and diagrams stay focused on your code.
#
# Examples (uncomment and adjust):
# node_modules
# vendor
# .venv
# venv
# dist
# build
# CodeVisualizer
# Facade V3
# enterprise
# community
# odoo-venv
# __pycache__
